HEADWORD: Palinurus
<hw>Pal`inu"rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from L.
<etsep>Palinurus</etsep>, the pilot of Aeneas.]</ety> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>An instrument for obtaining directly, without calculation, the true
bearing of the sun, and thence the variation of the compass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palisade</ent>⟦br⟧
